&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has been created through new investment to develop the service and the offer within Solihull Early Intervention.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Solihull Early Intervention provides a service, 7 days per week for those who are experiencing a first episode of Psychosis and also those Young people who are at Risk of developing Psychosis (ARMS).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, dynamic, self-motivated care co-ordinator to work as part of a multi-disciplinary team delivering evidence based interventions across the full age range. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applications are invited from a variety of professional back grounds to contribute to the expert knowledge and experience that already exists within the team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you require any information please do not hesitate to call myself, Steve Harrison (CYP HUB, Clinical Services Manager) on 0121 301 4967. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Namestephen harrisonJob titleCYP HUB Clinical Services managerEmail addressstephen.harrison10@nhs.netTelephone number0121 301 4967&lt;/p&gt;
